The paper deals with image classification using deep learning techniques, specifically capsule layers and long-short term memory layers with distributed attention. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as attention, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with classification of land use, which may involve text classification techniques, suggesting that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
